HomeAbout UsDean's Council
Dean's Council
Working together for SPEA’s strategic advancementEstablished in 2009, members of SPEA Dean’s Council serve as advisors and ambassadors for the school. Composed of scientists, attorneys, entrepreneurs, public servants, and business leaders, more than half of the council members have substantial public and nonprofit experience, including several who have served in the Executive Office of the President of the United States.2017 Dean's Council Meetings:
 March 23-24 and September 7-8
The Council is charged with advising me on strategic direction and opportunities, serving as ambassadors, and assisting with resource development for the school. We welcome this distinguished group and look forward to working together to effect advancements of the school’s curricula, scholarship, and more.—John D. Graham, SPEA Dean
