SPEA School of Public and Environmental Affairs





HomeAbout Us
About Us
Leading the Way to a Better WorldWalk through the doors of SPEA and you’ll feel it. There’s an energy here that you won’t find anywhere else. A certainty that what we’re doing has the power to create change. We’re committed to working together to make a better world.
What is SPEA? The School of Public and Environmental Affairs is a nationally ranked academic institution located on the campus of Indiana University and home to a Masters of Public Affairs program that’s ranked number one in the nation.
We bring together management skills, science, policy analysis, and the humanities. We focus on governing, managing, and leading. We prepare students to address the complex issues that face society today—issues one field of study alone can't solve.
And the world has noticed. We’ve been recognized many times over for our unique programs and outstanding faculty.
See our rankings Take a virtual tour Learn about the O'Neill Graduate Center

Learn why SPEA is right for youUndergraduateLead for the greater good right out of collegeMastersTake on a leadership role in any employment sectorDoctoralLead for the greater good at an advanced level 
Learn about SPEA in your own languageSpanishEspañolMandarinVietnamese
SPEA creates leaders for every sector of the economyOur programs run the gamut from public policy to environmental management and from healthcare administration to arts administration.
Our graduates thrive in governmental agencies, private corporations, and nonprofit organizations—and often move seamlessly among all three.
SPEA made me career readyMegan Caldwell, Bachelor of Science in Policy Analysis, 2012, Health4America Fellow"SPEA’s focus on equipping their students with a complete tool kit set me up for success after graduation. The ability to take classes in finance, accounting, computer processing, analysis, and public speaking, as well as specific topical classes, provided me with strong hard and soft skills."
Learn more about how SPEA can help you lead for the greater goodExplore our research Dive into the student experience
A legacy of leadershipA look at SPEA's beginnings, founded in 1972.







